1
00:01:36,729 --> 00:01:40,140
[Born to Be Alive]

2
00:01:40,180 --> 00:01:43,229
[Episode 20]

3
00:01:44,039 --> 00:01:44,500
You just

4
00:01:44,500 --> 00:01:46,900
criticized our County Finance Department

5
00:01:47,009 --> 00:01:47,789
for irregularities

6
00:01:47,789 --> 00:01:48,870
in fund usage.

7
00:01:49,509 --> 00:01:50,310
I accept that.

8
00:01:52,210 --> 00:01:53,500
But the root cause

9
00:01:53,590 --> 00:01:54,039
is not

10
00:01:54,070 --> 00:01:55,590
our cadres acting rashly

11
00:01:55,700 --> 00:01:56,780
or selfishly.

12
00:01:57,700 --> 00:01:58,960
It is out of necessity.

13
00:01:59,700 --> 00:02:00,120
I believe

14
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:01,560
our comrades in the county

15
00:02:01,560 --> 00:02:03,090
are dedicated to the public

16
00:02:03,540 --> 00:02:05,670
and can withstand any investigation.

17
00:02:11,750 --> 00:02:12,680
Director Zhang.

18
00:02:13,850 --> 00:02:14,730
What do you say?

19
00:02:15,340 --> 00:02:15,870
Okay.

20
00:02:16,360 --> 00:02:17,410
The Municipal Economic Commission

21
00:02:17,410 --> 00:02:19,740
will use this survey's findings

22
00:02:19,780 --> 00:02:22,380
to draft support policies
as soon as possible.

23
00:02:25,150 --> 00:02:26,260
The Municipal Planning Commission

24
00:02:26,260 --> 00:02:27,460
will also quickly review

25
00:02:27,460 --> 00:02:28,410
relevant

26
00:02:28,440 --> 00:02:30,010
approval matters

27
00:02:30,130 --> 00:02:31,870
and offer full support.

28
00:02:34,590 --> 00:02:35,870
Thank you all

29
00:02:35,900 --> 00:02:37,560
for your concern and support.

30
00:02:38,950 --> 00:02:40,680
It is a fact that the local level

31
00:02:41,360 --> 00:02:42,820
faces many difficulties.

32
00:02:43,160 --> 00:02:44,260
But we can't just

33
00:02:44,290 --> 00:02:45,690
because of difficulties

34
00:02:46,390 --> 00:02:47,590
violate discipline.

35
00:02:50,090 --> 00:02:50,829
Comrade Chen Cheng

36
00:02:50,829 --> 00:02:52,290
and Comrade Lin Peisheng,

37
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:54,840
regarding the issues mentioned above,

38
00:02:54,840 --> 00:02:56,090
you must submit a profound self-criticism

39
00:02:56,090 --> 00:02:57,810
to the city government soon.

40
00:02:59,870 --> 00:03:01,000
I think this survey

41
00:03:01,290 --> 00:03:02,820
has been very significant.

42
00:03:04,130 --> 00:03:05,130
I also hope

43
00:03:05,640 --> 00:03:07,440
that Mazhi County's future work

44
00:03:07,900 --> 00:03:09,300
will be more efficient

45
00:03:10,900 --> 00:03:11,760
and compliant.

46
00:03:13,130 --> 00:03:13,620
Good.

47
00:03:13,780 --> 00:03:14,710
Vice Mayor Zhao.

48
00:03:15,370 --> 00:03:16,180
There is one more thing

49
00:03:16,180 --> 00:03:17,440
I need to report to you.

50
00:03:19,220 --> 00:03:19,740
Okay.

51
00:03:20,410 --> 00:03:20,940
Go ahead.

52
00:03:21,590 --> 00:03:22,079
We...

53
00:03:23,210 --> 00:03:24,200
Let me say it.

54
00:03:25,560 --> 00:03:26,220
I'll say it.

55
00:03:27,900 --> 00:03:28,960
I've been handling

56
00:03:29,010 --> 00:03:30,280
this matter,

57
00:03:31,370 --> 00:03:33,170
so I can explain it more clearly.

58
00:03:37,280 --> 00:03:38,190
Last winter,

59
00:03:38,710 --> 00:03:39,750
Mazhi County

60
00:03:40,079 --> 00:03:41,090
experienced

61
00:03:41,140 --> 00:03:42,410
5 heavy snowfalls.

62
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:44,040
Accumulated precipitation

63
00:03:44,040 --> 00:03:45,300
was 19.4 millimeters,

64
00:03:45,710 --> 00:03:47,640
causing a moderate snow disaster.

65
00:03:47,730 --> 00:03:48,990
The snow-covered area

66
00:03:49,100 --> 00:03:50,030
in the county reached

67
00:03:50,030 --> 00:03:51,560
12,000 square kilometers.

68
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:54,350
Two animal husbandry townships

69
00:03:54,350 --> 00:03:56,010
were severely affected.

70
00:03:56,329 --> 00:03:56,990
Therefore,

71
00:03:57,300 --> 00:03:58,730
the County People's Congress

72
00:03:58,730 --> 00:04:01,260
proposed
an animal husbandry tax exemption.

73
00:04:01,320 --> 00:04:02,190
We hope

74
00:04:02,490 --> 00:04:03,940
that the higher tax authorities

75
00:04:03,940 --> 00:04:04,990
can grant

76
00:04:05,080 --> 00:04:06,480
a three-year exemption.

77
00:04:06,980 --> 00:04:07,580
This would

78
00:04:07,870 --> 00:04:08,980
give the herdsmen

79
00:04:09,090 --> 00:04:10,910
time to recover.

80
00:04:12,210 --> 00:04:13,670
We also earnestly request

81
00:04:13,900 --> 00:04:15,560
the higher-level finance department

82
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:16,760
to provide our county

83
00:04:17,240 --> 00:04:19,700
additional targeted financial subsidies.

84
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:25,870
We also know

85
00:04:26,770 --> 00:04:27,330
that if

86
00:04:28,070 --> 00:04:29,430
a long-term exemption

87
00:04:29,940 --> 00:04:30,740
is difficult,

88
00:04:31,380 --> 00:04:33,040
then a short-term exemption,

89
00:04:33,280 --> 00:04:34,659
like for 6 months first and then a year,

90
00:04:34,659 --> 00:04:35,520
will also work.

91
00:04:44,760 --> 00:04:45,580
Chief Song.

92
00:04:47,220 --> 00:04:48,010
You need to take

93
00:04:48,010 --> 00:04:50,140
this tax reduction matter seriously.

94
00:04:52,810 --> 00:04:53,740
Regarding the animal husbandry tax issue

95
00:04:53,740 --> 00:04:55,270
raised by County Mayor Lin,

96
00:04:55,860 --> 00:04:57,180
the County Local Taxation Bureau

97
00:04:57,180 --> 00:04:58,840
has already reported it to us.

98
00:04:59,270 --> 00:05:00,590
We are also actively communicating

99
00:05:00,590 --> 00:05:01,670
with the provincial bureau.

100
00:05:01,670 --> 00:05:02,370
Chief Song.

101
00:05:04,390 --> 00:05:05,010
I know

102
00:05:06,600 --> 00:05:08,280
this is difficult.

103
00:05:08,850 --> 00:05:09,680
But the animal husbandry tax

104
00:05:09,680 --> 00:05:11,280
affects two ends of the line.

105
00:05:11,780 --> 00:05:13,480
One end is the herdsmen's burden,

106
00:05:13,480 --> 00:05:14,220
and the other

107
00:05:14,750 --> 00:05:16,860
is the operation
of the County Finance Department.

108
00:05:16,860 --> 00:05:17,430
But in the 2 animal husbandry townships

109
00:05:17,430 --> 00:05:19,190
hit hardest by the disaster,

110
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:21,870
the herdsmen have lost

111
00:05:21,870 --> 00:05:23,400
over half their livestock.

112
00:05:23,950 --> 00:05:25,400
Some households
have barely any livestock left—

113
00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:27,000
less than one in ten remains.

114
00:05:27,500 --> 00:05:28,390
Following that,

115
00:05:28,390 --> 00:05:29,390
medical care,

116
00:05:29,800 --> 00:05:30,750
schooling,

117
00:05:30,780 --> 00:05:31,980
and other safeguards

118
00:05:32,630 --> 00:05:33,870
will fall apart.

119
00:05:35,490 --> 00:05:36,350
In our county's

120
00:05:36,460 --> 00:05:38,060
primary and middle schools,

121
00:05:38,430 --> 00:05:40,110
12 students have already

122
00:05:41,170 --> 00:05:42,360
dropped out to work.

123
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:46,650
Teachers went to the herdsmen's homes

124
00:05:46,650 --> 00:05:47,980
to persuade the children.

125
00:05:47,980 --> 00:05:49,530
They wanted to bring them back.

126
00:05:49,530 --> 00:05:51,990
The children want to come back
to school too.

127
00:05:52,880 --> 00:05:55,080
But their families are in dire straits.

128
00:06:00,550 --> 00:06:02,210
Please understand, leaders.

129
00:06:03,410 --> 00:06:04,410
It's not just that the county

130
00:06:04,410 --> 00:06:06,180
wants to reduce the tax burden.

131
00:06:07,170 --> 00:06:08,940
Mainly, after this snow disaster,

132
00:06:08,940 --> 00:06:11,010
although herdsmen have received subsidies,

133
00:06:11,010 --> 00:06:12,070
it still takes time

134
00:06:12,500 --> 00:06:14,430
to replenish the cattle and sheep.

135
00:06:15,980 --> 00:06:16,660
So,

136
00:06:18,020 --> 00:06:18,860
here,

137
00:06:18,920 --> 00:06:20,250
I implore the Vice Mayor

138
00:06:20,310 --> 00:06:21,840
and all department leaders

139
00:06:21,840 --> 00:06:23,240
to look into this quickly

140
00:06:23,350 --> 00:06:25,080
and handle it as a special case.

141
00:06:41,790 --> 00:06:43,560
Regarding the animal husbandry tax,

142
00:06:43,560 --> 00:06:45,290
the fiscal and tax departments

143
00:06:45,420 --> 00:06:47,550
must appeal to the higher authorities

144
00:06:47,870 --> 00:06:49,530
and report to
the Provincial Local Taxation Bureau

145
00:06:49,530 --> 00:06:51,100
and the Department of Finance again

146
00:06:51,100 --> 00:06:53,700
to strive for
the maximum possible reduction.

147
00:06:53,700 --> 00:06:54,210
Yes.

148
00:06:54,280 --> 00:06:55,010
In addition,

149
00:06:55,190 --> 00:06:56,460
our government departments

150
00:06:56,460 --> 00:06:57,480
must mobilize

151
00:06:57,920 --> 00:06:58,950
to raise funds

152
00:06:58,980 --> 00:07:00,340
and urgently allocate some livestock

153
00:07:00,340 --> 00:07:02,200
to the animal husbandry counties

154
00:07:02,480 --> 00:07:04,010
for the affected herdsmen.

155
00:07:06,860 --> 00:07:07,720
We must quickly

156
00:07:08,090 --> 00:07:09,890
restore the livestock numbers.

157
00:07:10,970 --> 00:07:11,570
That is the way

158
00:07:11,570 --> 00:07:14,010
to cure both the symptoms
and the root cause.

159
00:07:14,010 --> 00:07:15,010
What do you think?

160
00:07:15,270 --> 00:07:15,520
Right.

161
00:07:15,520 --> 00:07:15,870
Right.

162
00:07:15,870 --> 00:07:16,370
Yes.

163
00:07:18,510 --> 00:07:19,110
Thank you.

164
00:07:19,560 --> 00:07:20,820
Thank you, Vice Mayor.

165
00:07:21,270 --> 00:07:22,070
On behalf of Mazhi County's

166
00:07:22,070 --> 00:07:23,570
26,000 cadres and people,

167
00:07:24,250 --> 00:07:24,870
I thank you, Vice Mayor,

168
00:07:24,870 --> 00:07:26,260
and all the leaders for your support.

169
00:07:26,260 --> 00:07:26,860
Thank you.

170
00:07:47,800 --> 00:07:48,730
Secretary Chen.

171
00:07:48,800 --> 00:07:50,130
Vice Mayor Zhao, goodbye.

172
00:07:50,130 --> 00:07:50,690
Goodbye.

173
00:07:52,070 --> 00:07:52,909
County Mayor Lin.

174
00:07:52,909 --> 00:07:53,570
Vice Mayor,

175
00:07:53,580 --> 00:07:54,710
have a safe journey.

176
00:07:58,630 --> 00:07:59,780
You've got guts.

177
00:08:07,030 --> 00:08:07,470
Come on.

178
00:08:07,470 --> 00:08:07,860
Good work.

179
00:08:07,860 --> 00:08:08,390
Goodbye.

180
00:08:32,490 --> 00:08:33,130
Lin.

181
00:08:37,130 --> 00:08:38,620
You're starting to look like
your old self.

182
00:08:38,620 --> 00:08:40,230
The County Mayor on horseback.

183
00:08:40,230 --> 00:08:40,789
Cairen,

184
00:08:40,820 --> 00:08:41,570
how are you?

185
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:43,250
County Mayor Lin, you're here.

186
00:08:43,250 --> 00:08:44,039
You're busy.

187
00:08:44,910 --> 00:08:46,110
I'll go pour some tea.

188
00:08:48,030 --> 00:08:48,770
Rest a bit.

189
00:08:58,320 --> 00:08:58,870
Thank you.

190
00:08:58,870 --> 00:08:59,320
Cairen.

191
00:08:59,320 --> 00:08:59,920
Not at all.

192
00:09:00,270 --> 00:09:00,630
Here.

193
00:09:01,530 --> 00:09:02,330
Have some tea.

194
00:09:07,790 --> 00:09:08,790
County Mayor Lin.

195
00:09:09,630 --> 00:09:10,830
You really have guts.

196
00:09:11,620 --> 00:09:12,680
Are you mocking me?

197
00:09:15,570 --> 00:09:16,030
Don't pull

198
00:09:16,030 --> 00:09:17,270
such a long face.

199
00:09:18,320 --> 00:09:18,730
Here.

200
00:09:19,930 --> 00:09:21,410
The leader was praising you.

201
00:09:21,410 --> 00:09:22,410
It's a good thing.

202
00:09:25,440 --> 00:09:26,200
I hope so.

203
00:09:27,780 --> 00:09:28,980
If you were so scared,

204
00:09:29,150 --> 00:09:31,360
why did you fight to speak at the meeting?

205
00:09:31,360 --> 00:09:32,170
You could have just let me do the talking.

206
00:09:32,170 --> 00:09:33,030
Wouldn't that have been better?

207
00:09:33,030 --> 00:09:33,840
Let you speak?

208
00:09:34,100 --> 00:09:34,640
I was afraid you

209
00:09:34,640 --> 00:09:35,900
would screw things up.

210
00:09:36,260 --> 00:09:37,580
With your big mouth,

211
00:09:37,650 --> 00:09:38,200
right from the start,

212
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:39,720
you would take shots at the Vice Mayor.

213
00:09:39,720 --> 00:09:40,450
You even said

214
00:09:40,580 --> 00:09:41,510
that all comrades
in the County Party Committee

215
00:09:41,510 --> 00:09:43,270
can withstand any investigation.

216
00:09:43,270 --> 00:09:44,030
Aren't you afraid
the Discipline Inspection Commission

217
00:09:44,030 --> 00:09:45,290
will actually send someone?

218
00:09:45,290 --> 00:09:46,150
I'm not afraid.

219
00:09:47,840 --> 00:09:48,390
Why?

220
00:09:49,030 --> 00:09:49,890
Can't you withstand an investigation?

221
00:09:49,890 --> 00:09:51,290
You're the one who can't.

222
00:09:51,770 --> 00:09:53,500
I'm just afraid of the trouble.

223
00:09:53,650 --> 00:09:54,570
One trouble like you in the county

224
00:09:54,570 --> 00:09:55,170
is enough.

225
00:09:58,940 --> 00:09:59,620
Lin.

226
00:10:01,170 --> 00:10:01,720
When the municipal funding

227
00:10:01,720 --> 00:10:03,080
comes through,

228
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:05,600
you have to leave some for us.

229
00:10:07,120 --> 00:10:08,580
The Mountain Patrol
is self-funded and self-supporting.

230
00:10:08,580 --> 00:10:09,810
The County Party Committee decided this.

231
00:10:09,810 --> 00:10:11,470
You can't back out on this now.

232
00:10:11,820 --> 00:10:13,050
Then that 100,000
from the Department of Forestry,

233
00:10:13,050 --> 00:10:14,310
you have to give it back to us.

234
00:10:14,310 --> 00:10:15,750
That should have been ours long ago.

235
00:10:15,750 --> 00:10:16,630
90,000.

236
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:19,700
Fine.

237
00:10:20,270 --> 00:10:20,890
90,000.

238
00:10:22,070 --> 00:10:22,700
By the way,

239
00:10:23,220 --> 00:10:24,150
tell Danzhou

240
00:10:24,170 --> 00:10:26,000
to stop going out for mineral exploration
these days.

241
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:28,060
It's too dangerous in the mountains.

242
00:10:28,740 --> 00:10:29,800
There you go again.

243
00:10:31,440 --> 00:10:32,510
I'm serious.

244
00:10:33,390 --> 00:10:34,670
Last time we went into the mountains,

245
00:10:34,670 --> 00:10:35,130
we ran into

246
00:10:35,130 --> 00:10:36,790
a fairly large criminal gang.

247
00:10:37,240 --> 00:10:38,150
They were different from those poachers

248
00:10:38,150 --> 00:10:39,530
and fossickers.

249
00:10:44,360 --> 00:10:46,420
Duo, I've been thinking a lot lately.

250
00:10:48,180 --> 00:10:49,110
What year

251
00:10:49,460 --> 00:10:50,330
did we meet?

252
00:10:50,360 --> 00:10:51,170
1979?

253
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:56,000
1978.

254
00:10:59,510 --> 00:11:03,310
The year of the Third Plenary Session
of the 11th Central Committee.

255
00:11:04,400 --> 00:11:05,310
You had just graduated

256
00:11:05,310 --> 00:11:06,570
and were assigned here

257
00:11:07,210 --> 00:11:09,670
to reconstruct the Qinghai-Tibet Highway.

258
00:11:10,860 --> 00:11:11,500
At that time,

259
00:11:11,500 --> 00:11:14,100
I was the deputy director
of the Quduo Commune.

260
00:11:14,270 --> 00:11:14,870
I sent you guys

261
00:11:14,870 --> 00:11:15,910
over a dozen yaks.

262
00:11:16,080 --> 00:11:16,880
Right, right.

263
00:11:20,720 --> 00:11:21,500
1978.

264
00:11:24,220 --> 00:11:25,950
For the first time in human history,

265
00:11:25,950 --> 00:11:28,150
in a high-altitude permafrost region,

266
00:11:28,900 --> 00:11:30,430
asphalt pavement was laid.

267
00:11:33,260 --> 00:11:34,130
How high did we need to build

268
00:11:34,130 --> 00:11:35,170
the roadbed

269
00:11:35,510 --> 00:11:37,100
to protect the permafrost

270
00:11:37,120 --> 00:11:38,740
from the ground heat?

271
00:11:40,060 --> 00:11:40,830
What kind of

272
00:11:40,860 --> 00:11:42,720
drainage facilities were needed

273
00:11:43,270 --> 00:11:44,520
to prevent surface water

274
00:11:44,520 --> 00:11:45,980
from eroding the roadbed?

275
00:11:46,600 --> 00:11:47,770
There was no international experience

276
00:11:47,770 --> 00:11:48,550
to refer to.

277
00:11:50,080 --> 00:11:50,750
Every day,

278
00:11:50,860 --> 00:11:52,080
I followed my mentor,

279
00:11:53,270 --> 00:11:54,130
doing surveys,

280
00:11:54,750 --> 00:11:56,210
conducting experiments,

281
00:11:56,630 --> 00:11:58,430
and supervising construction.

282
00:11:58,880 --> 00:12:00,480
We were up to our ears in work.

283
00:12:00,960 --> 00:12:01,680
Back then,

284
00:12:01,800 --> 00:12:02,890
during breaks,

285
00:12:03,860 --> 00:12:05,010
I went to a nearby temple

286
00:12:05,010 --> 00:12:06,010
to ask for some tea

287
00:12:07,570 --> 00:12:09,370
and chat with the old Lama there.

288
00:12:10,070 --> 00:12:10,670
I said,

289
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:14,200
"I'm sorry

290
00:12:14,780 --> 00:12:16,460
about all the clanging and banging
every day,

291
00:12:16,460 --> 00:12:18,460
really sorry for the disturbance."

292
00:12:19,320 --> 00:12:19,860
The old Lama

293
00:12:19,860 --> 00:12:21,050
gave me a Thangka.

294
00:12:22,500 --> 00:12:24,010
It was painted by his disciple,

295
00:12:24,010 --> 00:12:24,940
Gyatso.

296
00:12:26,830 --> 00:12:27,720
Gyatso froze to death

297
00:12:27,720 --> 00:12:29,250
on his pilgrimage to Lhasa.

298
00:12:32,050 --> 00:12:33,910
The old Lama held my hand and said,

299
00:12:35,290 --> 00:12:36,120
"Young man,

300
00:12:37,950 --> 00:12:39,880
what you are building is not a road.

301
00:12:41,150 --> 00:12:42,750
It's Gyatso's prayer wheel,

302
00:12:43,170 --> 00:12:44,530
Lhamo's medicine chest,

303
00:12:44,530 --> 00:12:45,890
and the textbooks in Dondrup's schoolbag

304
00:12:45,890 --> 00:12:46,930
that won't be ruined

305
00:12:46,930 --> 00:12:48,060
by snow water."

306
00:12:52,980 --> 00:12:53,750
In 1985,

307
00:12:55,720 --> 00:12:56,800
the Qinghai-Tibet Highway's

308
00:12:56,800 --> 00:12:59,060
blacktop pavement was fully completed.

309
00:12:59,250 --> 00:13:00,380
I chose to stay here.

310
00:13:02,480 --> 00:13:04,340
And I've stayed for over 10 years.

311
00:13:06,080 --> 00:13:06,740
That Thangka

312
00:13:06,740 --> 00:13:07,210
is still

313
00:13:07,240 --> 00:13:08,300
hanging in my home,

314
00:13:09,460 --> 00:13:10,860
reminding me constantly

315
00:13:11,840 --> 00:13:14,100
that this is the meaning of development.

316
00:13:14,440 --> 00:13:16,500
Duo, I've been here for over 10 years.

317
00:13:17,910 --> 00:13:19,100
The average life expectancy
in pastoral areas

318
00:13:19,100 --> 00:13:20,360
has risen from under 55

319
00:13:20,660 --> 00:13:22,140
to over 60.

320
00:13:23,290 --> 00:13:24,320
The youth illiteracy rate

321
00:13:24,320 --> 00:13:25,660
has dropped from over 60%

322
00:13:25,660 --> 00:13:27,190
to 20%.

323
00:13:28,630 --> 00:13:29,480
This is the change

324
00:13:29,480 --> 00:13:32,140
development has brought
to the pastoral areas.

325
00:13:33,770 --> 00:13:34,560
I know.

326
00:13:36,790 --> 00:13:38,190
You came up to the plateau

327
00:13:38,580 --> 00:13:39,790
and did so many good things.

328
00:13:39,790 --> 00:13:41,240
Then why are you standing in our way

329
00:13:41,240 --> 00:13:41,930
and forbidding us

330
00:13:41,930 --> 00:13:43,060
from doing all this?

331
00:13:43,790 --> 00:13:44,980
Do you want to go back
to pre-liberation times,

332
00:13:44,980 --> 00:13:46,580
back to a primitive society?

333
00:13:49,670 --> 00:13:51,000
I came to see you today

334
00:13:51,550 --> 00:13:52,360
because there are some things

335
00:13:52,360 --> 00:13:54,020
I couldn't say at the meeting.

336
00:13:56,380 --> 00:13:57,010
Do you think

337
00:13:57,010 --> 00:13:58,750
I'm setting up
the Economic Development Zone

338
00:13:58,750 --> 00:13:59,840
just to build my record

339
00:13:59,840 --> 00:14:00,840
and get promoted?

340
00:14:02,650 --> 00:14:04,380
Others might think that of you.

341
00:14:04,960 --> 00:14:05,980
But I don't.

342
00:14:07,580 --> 00:14:08,000
I know

343
00:14:08,030 --> 00:14:09,220
your feelings for the Tibetan people

344
00:14:09,220 --> 00:14:09,940
are real.

345
00:14:13,150 --> 00:14:13,750
Thank you.

346
00:14:16,670 --> 00:14:17,270
But after all,

347
00:14:17,270 --> 00:14:18,470
you are not from here.

348
00:14:20,670 --> 00:14:21,940
Sooner or later,

349
00:14:22,700 --> 00:14:23,720
you will be transferred

350
00:14:23,720 --> 00:14:24,920
and leave this place.

351
00:14:26,450 --> 00:14:27,510
But my home is here.

352
00:14:28,640 --> 00:14:29,670
I won't leave.

353
00:14:32,610 --> 00:14:33,550
Duo, do you think

354
00:14:33,580 --> 00:14:34,340
I have no affection

355
00:14:34,340 --> 00:14:35,200
for this land?

356
00:14:37,120 --> 00:14:37,530
Yes.

357
00:14:37,630 --> 00:14:38,690
I wasn't born here.

358
00:14:38,950 --> 00:14:39,720
But I have lived here

359
00:14:39,720 --> 00:14:41,130
for over 10 years.

360
00:14:42,450 --> 00:14:43,460
This place is actually

361
00:14:43,460 --> 00:14:44,520
the same as my home.

362
00:14:47,070 --> 00:14:48,070
It's not the same.

363
00:14:49,790 --> 00:14:51,920
This isn't just the home of the herders

364
00:14:52,020 --> 00:14:53,220
and the Mazhi people,

365
00:14:54,240 --> 00:14:55,570
but also the home of the Tibetan antelope

366
00:14:55,570 --> 00:14:57,070
and all wild animals.

367
00:14:58,500 --> 00:14:59,670
They can't speak.

368
00:14:59,930 --> 00:15:01,660
They won't file reports to you.

369
00:15:03,400 --> 00:15:04,900
If we do it your way

370
00:15:05,240 --> 00:15:05,980
and develop

371
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:06,900
everywhere

372
00:15:08,700 --> 00:15:10,100
in Mazhi,

373
00:15:10,860 --> 00:15:11,900
in 100 years,

374
00:15:13,600 --> 00:15:14,530
we will be gone,

375
00:15:15,860 --> 00:15:16,950
and the Tibetan antelope and wild animals

376
00:15:16,950 --> 00:15:17,880
will be gone too.

377
00:15:18,840 --> 00:15:19,890
Qinghai's sacred mountains and holy lakes

378
00:15:19,890 --> 00:15:20,750
will be gone.

379
00:15:22,120 --> 00:15:23,720
Whose home will this be then?

380
00:15:46,030 --> 00:15:46,980
The construction of the development zone

381
00:15:46,980 --> 00:15:48,100
must proceed.

382
00:15:58,060 --> 00:15:59,490
I won't give up halfway.

383
00:16:01,830 --> 00:16:02,610
I still insist on the idea

384
00:16:02,610 --> 00:16:03,870
of building a reserve.

385
00:16:15,020 --> 00:16:15,800
County Mayor Lin,

386
00:16:15,800 --> 00:16:17,260
won't you stay for dinner?

387
00:16:40,620 --> 00:16:41,550
Hello, Ms. Kang.

388
00:16:41,550 --> 00:16:41,990
Director Zhang.

389
00:16:41,990 --> 00:16:42,370
Okay.

390
00:16:49,320 --> 00:16:50,390
Mom, you're back.

391
00:16:51,340 --> 00:16:52,080
Cooking?

392
00:16:52,460 --> 00:16:53,370
Almost done.

393
00:16:56,390 --> 00:16:57,670
Why are you home?

394
00:16:58,250 --> 00:16:58,910
Didn't you go check out

395
00:16:58,910 --> 00:16:59,820
the storefront today?

396
00:16:59,820 --> 00:17:00,870
How did it go?

397
00:17:02,270 --> 00:17:03,670
Why the silence?

398
00:17:05,460 --> 00:17:06,720
Why the long face?

399
00:17:13,339 --> 00:17:14,040
Bai Chun.

400
00:17:14,680 --> 00:17:16,609
The work assignment came through?

401
00:17:16,720 --> 00:17:18,119
Yes. Victory Saltworks.

402
00:17:18,700 --> 00:17:20,349
Victory Saltworks?

403
00:17:21,750 --> 00:17:23,680
Is there such a place in our county?

404
00:17:25,230 --> 00:17:26,740
I think I've heard of it.

405
00:17:26,770 --> 00:17:27,400
Mom,

406
00:17:27,500 --> 00:17:28,380
don't you remember?

407
00:17:28,380 --> 00:17:29,220
When I was in middle school,

408
00:17:29,220 --> 00:17:31,180
a classmate's dad came for treatment.

409
00:17:31,180 --> 00:17:32,430
He didn't pay with money or meat,

410
00:17:32,430 --> 00:17:33,690
but gave 2 bags of salt.

411
00:17:33,740 --> 00:17:34,440
After that, our hospital

412
00:17:34,440 --> 00:17:35,900
didn't buy salt for a year.

413
00:17:37,360 --> 00:17:38,170
Right, right.

414
00:17:38,970 --> 00:17:39,550
He was

415
00:17:39,570 --> 00:17:41,050
from the Victory Saltworks.

416
00:17:41,050 --> 00:17:41,960
I remember now.

417
00:17:45,350 --> 00:17:46,680
That's really far.

418
00:17:46,880 --> 00:17:48,140
Almost 300 kilometers.

419
00:17:48,140 --> 00:17:49,800
It takes 10 hours to get there.

420
00:17:53,380 --> 00:17:54,750
When do you leave?

421
00:17:55,010 --> 00:17:56,500
They said in about 2 weeks.

422
00:17:56,530 --> 00:17:58,330
A car will come to pick me up then.

423
00:17:58,470 --> 00:17:59,180
Bai Ji.

424
00:17:59,850 --> 00:18:00,910
Serve the noodles.

425
00:18:08,990 --> 00:18:09,510
Mom.

426
00:18:10,360 --> 00:18:10,900
Taste it.

427
00:18:11,740 --> 00:18:13,330
I used my own rendered lard.

428
00:18:20,810 --> 00:18:21,240
Here.

429
00:18:24,240 --> 00:18:24,740
Chun.

430
00:18:25,440 --> 00:18:26,920
You're such an excellent soldier.

431
00:18:26,920 --> 00:18:28,320
How could you be assigned

432
00:18:28,770 --> 00:18:29,920
to a place like that?

433
00:18:30,590 --> 00:18:32,250
I think there must be a mistake.

434
00:18:32,250 --> 00:18:32,850
Mom,

435
00:18:33,160 --> 00:18:33,890
why don't you

436
00:18:34,170 --> 00:18:35,580
go ask Uncle Lin?

437
00:18:35,730 --> 00:18:36,860
Ask what?

438
00:18:37,950 --> 00:18:39,570
For us demobilized soldiers,

439
00:18:39,570 --> 00:18:40,420
this

440
00:18:40,440 --> 00:18:41,900
is the placement policy this year.

441
00:18:41,900 --> 00:18:42,950
Anyway,

442
00:18:43,060 --> 00:18:44,540
it's a state-run factory.

443
00:18:44,700 --> 00:18:46,070
It's a formal job.

444
00:18:47,230 --> 00:18:48,850
If you ask Mom to ask Uncle Lin,

445
00:18:48,850 --> 00:18:50,070
what can he do?

446
00:18:50,110 --> 00:18:51,570
Find me a unit separately?

447
00:18:51,880 --> 00:18:53,280
What would others think?

448
00:18:53,960 --> 00:18:55,030
But you've earned merits

449
00:18:55,030 --> 00:18:55,550
and are a Party Member.

450
00:18:55,550 --> 00:18:56,480
The leaders said

451
00:18:57,070 --> 00:18:58,050
it is to improve

452
00:18:58,070 --> 00:18:59,530
the quality of the saltworks staff

453
00:18:59,530 --> 00:19:00,420
that they decided on

454
00:19:00,420 --> 00:19:01,190
this plan.

455
00:19:08,060 --> 00:19:08,790
If you ask me,

456
00:19:09,570 --> 00:19:10,570
you shouldn't go.

457
00:19:11,310 --> 00:19:12,920
Just run the restaurant here with me.

458
00:19:12,920 --> 00:19:14,620
It's much better than some saltworks.

459
00:19:14,620 --> 00:19:16,120
It's a market economy now.

460
00:19:16,680 --> 00:19:18,700
Look at my sister and brother-in-law.

461
00:19:18,700 --> 00:19:19,210
They

462
00:19:19,240 --> 00:19:20,350
would rather sleep on the floor

463
00:19:20,350 --> 00:19:21,610
to be their own bosses.

464
00:19:22,480 --> 00:19:23,350
You were in the army

465
00:19:23,350 --> 00:19:24,460
training for so many years.

466
00:19:24,460 --> 00:19:25,800
If you go to the saltworks,

467
00:19:25,800 --> 00:19:27,130
what skills can you use?

468
00:19:27,720 --> 00:19:28,450
Besides,

469
00:19:30,270 --> 00:19:31,880
you haven't been home for years.

470
00:19:31,880 --> 00:19:33,730
You should stay and keep Mom company.

471
00:19:33,730 --> 00:19:34,390
Look at you.

472
00:19:34,400 --> 00:19:35,220
You'll be sent

473
00:19:35,240 --> 00:19:36,770
300 kilometers away again.

474
00:19:38,120 --> 00:19:38,930
Who knows how long it'll be

475
00:19:38,930 --> 00:19:39,930
before you visit?

476
00:19:40,170 --> 00:19:40,910
Bai Ji.

477
00:19:43,790 --> 00:19:44,770
The army is the army.

478
00:19:44,770 --> 00:19:46,290
Civilian life is different.

479
00:19:46,290 --> 00:19:48,220
No matter how well your brother did
in the army,

480
00:19:48,220 --> 00:19:49,650
that page has turned.

481
00:19:52,460 --> 00:19:54,060
The saltworks job is stable.

482
00:19:54,070 --> 00:19:55,000
You can go there.

483
00:19:57,250 --> 00:19:58,930
Your brother wants to open a shop.

484
00:19:58,930 --> 00:20:00,200
If you want to help him

485
00:20:00,530 --> 00:20:01,570
and become a partner,

486
00:20:01,570 --> 00:20:02,970
I'll support you as well.

487
00:20:04,400 --> 00:20:05,250
In the end,

488
00:20:05,880 --> 00:20:07,080
how you take this step

489
00:20:07,510 --> 00:20:08,760
is up to you.

490
00:20:14,130 --> 00:20:14,950
The Chief said

491
00:20:15,110 --> 00:20:18,030
the Public Security Brigade
wants to transfer you back.

492
00:20:18,030 --> 00:20:18,790
I haven't finished investigating

493
00:20:18,790 --> 00:20:19,600
my current case.

494
00:20:19,600 --> 00:20:20,860
I can't transfer back.

495
00:20:21,640 --> 00:20:22,530
Young lady,

496
00:20:22,570 --> 00:20:23,910
you must have a goal.

497
00:20:24,610 --> 00:20:25,640
Your goal is not

498
00:20:26,270 --> 00:20:27,220
to stay with the Mountain Patrol

499
00:20:27,220 --> 00:20:28,080
forever, is it?

500
00:20:29,820 --> 00:20:30,820
My goal

501
00:20:31,810 --> 00:20:33,230
is to clear up the case

502
00:20:33,250 --> 00:20:34,160
at hand.

503
00:20:40,530 --> 00:20:41,540
I can't eat anymore.

504
00:20:41,540 --> 00:20:42,560
Eat more.

505
00:20:43,360 --> 00:20:45,030
I'm afraid I'll end up like you.

506
00:20:45,030 --> 00:20:46,090
I won't eat either.

507
00:20:48,140 --> 00:20:49,010
You said it.

508
00:20:49,210 --> 00:20:51,470
Don't ask to borrow meal tickets at noon.

509
00:20:52,860 --> 00:20:54,250
You're acting like a stranger.

510
00:20:54,250 --> 00:20:55,180
Like a stranger.

511
00:21:04,130 --> 00:21:05,250
[I don't know him.]

512
00:21:05,250 --> 00:21:06,380
[Guo Shun from the town's repair shop
fixed their driver's car once.]

513
00:21:06,400 --> 00:21:08,660
[I know Guo Shun. I heard about it
from him when we were talking.]

514
00:21:20,350 --> 00:21:24,630
[Where did you get
your gold mining tools?] [From Guo Shun.]

515
00:21:33,530 --> 00:21:34,480
Oh, Guo Shun.

516
00:21:35,050 --> 00:21:35,610
You're like a big pot

517
00:21:35,610 --> 00:21:36,570
trying to cram everything

518
00:21:36,570 --> 00:21:37,500
into your mouth.

519
00:21:38,190 --> 00:21:38,840
Guo Shun,

520
00:21:39,590 --> 00:21:40,610
do you think no one in Mazhi County

521
00:21:40,610 --> 00:21:41,570
knows you?

522
00:21:46,550 --> 00:21:48,480
[Guo Shun]

523
00:21:53,210 --> 00:21:53,840
Mr. Luo.

524
00:21:55,380 --> 00:21:55,950
Can I see

525
00:21:55,980 --> 00:21:57,180
Guo Shun's case file?

526
00:21:57,990 --> 00:21:59,190
Guo Shun's case file?

527
00:22:04,750 --> 00:22:05,400
That case was closed

528
00:22:05,400 --> 00:22:06,420
a long time ago.

529
00:22:07,180 --> 00:22:08,510
The shop was closed too.

530
00:22:09,340 --> 00:22:10,800
I want to take another look.

531
00:22:10,800 --> 00:22:13,260
It's related to the case
I'm investigating.

532
00:22:15,020 --> 00:22:16,020
That's not right.

533
00:22:17,070 --> 00:22:17,730
This case involves

534
00:22:17,730 --> 00:22:18,990
your brother.

535
00:22:19,010 --> 00:22:20,340
You're a related party.

536
00:22:20,350 --> 00:22:21,590
You can't see it under regulations.

537
00:22:21,590 --> 00:22:23,320
You need to report to the Chief.

538
00:22:24,280 --> 00:22:25,480
I'll just take a peek.

539
00:22:25,870 --> 00:22:27,040
You can watch me.

540
00:22:27,700 --> 00:22:28,400
It'll be quick.

541
00:22:28,400 --> 00:22:29,600
Don't tell the Chief.

542
00:22:32,810 --> 00:22:33,840
Well, well.

543
00:22:37,110 --> 00:22:37,780
Mr. Luo.

544
00:22:39,570 --> 00:22:41,110
This chocolate is delicious.

545
00:22:41,110 --> 00:22:42,310
It's sweet but not too rich.

546
00:22:42,310 --> 00:22:42,940
Taste it.

547
00:22:43,340 --> 00:22:44,170
Have one.

548
00:22:47,110 --> 00:22:48,010
It's pitch black.

549
00:22:48,010 --> 00:22:50,140
I can tell it's no good just by looking.

550
00:23:01,390 --> 00:23:02,870
This shop bought a lot of

551
00:23:02,900 --> 00:23:04,500
sheepskins from poachers.

552
00:23:07,070 --> 00:23:07,720
He likely had

553
00:23:07,720 --> 00:23:09,110
connections

554
00:23:09,130 --> 00:23:10,530
to a major poaching gang.

555
00:23:10,610 --> 00:23:11,240
Yeah.

556
00:23:11,420 --> 00:23:12,030
Didn't your brother

557
00:23:12,030 --> 00:23:13,190
go in with them?

558
00:23:14,230 --> 00:23:15,800
You're way off topic.

559
00:23:16,820 --> 00:23:18,480
I'm saying what's strange is,

560
00:23:18,940 --> 00:23:20,270
at his shop, not only sheepskins,

561
00:23:20,270 --> 00:23:21,360
explosives, and bullets—

562
00:23:21,360 --> 00:23:22,750
the usual evidence in such cases—

563
00:23:22,750 --> 00:23:24,030
were found,

564
00:23:25,400 --> 00:23:26,610
but his ledgers

565
00:23:26,640 --> 00:23:27,740
also showed

566
00:23:28,260 --> 00:23:29,520
he resold mercury.

567
00:23:30,670 --> 00:23:31,720
What is this for?

568
00:23:32,840 --> 00:23:33,510
Not sure.

569
00:23:34,180 --> 00:23:35,530
It's illegal anyway.

570
00:23:36,250 --> 00:23:37,780
The copper factory

571
00:23:37,810 --> 00:23:38,510
that illegally bought the mercury

572
00:23:38,510 --> 00:23:39,570
was also shut down.

573
00:23:40,360 --> 00:23:41,520
What did this factory

574
00:23:41,520 --> 00:23:42,630
use mercury for?

575
00:23:45,420 --> 00:23:47,180
To make silver-plated crafts.

576
00:23:54,400 --> 00:23:56,120
150 kilograms.

577
00:24:00,570 --> 00:24:02,160
The numbers don't add up.

578
00:24:03,110 --> 00:24:03,810
Look.

579
00:24:04,830 --> 00:24:06,590
The copper factory claimed

580
00:24:06,640 --> 00:24:08,770
they bought 150 kilograms of mercury.

581
00:24:08,950 --> 00:24:10,880
It was shut down in less than a week.

582
00:24:12,050 --> 00:24:13,460
Given this fact,

583
00:24:13,480 --> 00:24:14,350
we only found

584
00:24:14,380 --> 00:24:15,310
50 kilograms.

585
00:24:16,510 --> 00:24:17,970
That factory couldn't use

586
00:24:18,310 --> 00:24:19,720
100 kilograms in a week.

587
00:24:19,920 --> 00:24:21,250
So where did the rest go?

588
00:24:21,550 --> 00:24:22,570
They said it was lost.

589
00:24:22,570 --> 00:24:23,250
I guess they were not

590
00:24:23,250 --> 00:24:24,310
telling the truth.

591
00:24:36,860 --> 00:24:37,990
Can a book tell you

592
00:24:38,010 --> 00:24:39,410
where that mercury went?

593
00:24:41,400 --> 00:24:43,730
I think mercury can be used
to refine gold.

594
00:24:51,830 --> 00:24:52,770
Stop wiping.

595
00:24:54,740 --> 00:24:55,250
Ju.

596
00:24:56,310 --> 00:24:57,370
It's clean, right?

597
00:24:57,880 --> 00:24:59,200
If you keep wiping it like this every day,

598
00:24:59,200 --> 00:24:59,750
my car paint

599
00:24:59,750 --> 00:25:00,990
is going to rub off.

600
00:25:01,060 --> 00:25:01,950
Then tomorrow,

601
00:25:03,190 --> 00:25:04,450
I'll clean the inside.

602
00:25:08,400 --> 00:25:08,920
Ju.

603
00:25:09,540 --> 00:25:10,740
How's the case going?

604
00:25:12,740 --> 00:25:14,020
Are you my leader?

605
00:25:14,980 --> 00:25:15,480
Do you want me

606
00:25:15,480 --> 00:25:16,880
to write a report for you?

607
00:25:17,780 --> 00:25:18,960
No, no need.

608
00:25:21,160 --> 00:25:22,000
Get in!

609
00:25:22,350 --> 00:25:23,010
Okay!

610
00:25:27,810 --> 00:25:28,610
That mountain ahead,

611
00:25:28,610 --> 00:25:30,470
when was that big pit blasted out?

612
00:25:31,900 --> 00:25:34,160
While you were away these past few years.

613
00:25:34,440 --> 00:25:35,210
I didn't notice.

614
00:25:35,210 --> 00:25:36,660
It's a quarry now.

615
00:25:37,510 --> 00:25:38,510
The mountain from our childhood

616
00:25:38,510 --> 00:25:39,370
looked better.

617
00:25:40,270 --> 00:25:40,830
I could also say

618
00:25:40,830 --> 00:25:41,660
the firecrackers from our childhood

619
00:25:41,660 --> 00:25:42,390
were louder.

620
00:25:42,670 --> 00:25:43,930
My childhood friends

621
00:25:44,070 --> 00:25:44,940
all envied me

622
00:25:44,960 --> 00:25:46,620
for having a brother like you.

623
00:25:47,500 --> 00:25:48,770
What's there to envy?

624
00:25:49,790 --> 00:25:50,250
Back then,

625
00:25:50,250 --> 00:25:51,140
among us kids,

626
00:25:51,160 --> 00:25:52,140
you were the tallest,

627
00:25:52,140 --> 00:25:52,940
the fastest,

628
00:25:52,960 --> 00:25:54,000
and the best fighter.

629
00:25:54,000 --> 00:25:55,460
How could they not envy me?

630
00:25:55,710 --> 00:25:57,310
Too bad none of that matters.

631
00:25:58,770 --> 00:25:59,220
When you grow up,

632
00:25:59,220 --> 00:26:00,620
nobody cares about that.

633
00:26:06,220 --> 00:26:06,770
Chun.

634
00:26:09,010 --> 00:26:10,870
Let's run a restaurant together.

635
00:26:12,470 --> 00:26:13,830
You gave me all your money.

636
00:26:13,830 --> 00:26:14,610
This restaurant

637
00:26:14,610 --> 00:26:16,410
should rightfully be yours too.

638
00:26:17,670 --> 00:26:18,250
Besides,

639
00:26:18,830 --> 00:26:19,910
if you're there,

640
00:26:21,250 --> 00:26:22,780
I'll feel much more at ease.

641
00:26:25,240 --> 00:26:26,890
Then in the future,
I want not only a salary

642
00:26:26,890 --> 00:26:27,890
but also a bonus.

643
00:26:28,070 --> 00:26:29,180
That goes without saying!

644
00:26:29,180 --> 00:26:29,980
Of course!

645
00:26:30,000 --> 00:26:30,720
You promised.

646
00:26:30,720 --> 00:26:32,180
No going back on your word.

647
00:26:34,160 --> 00:26:35,380
But with Mom,

648
00:26:36,110 --> 00:26:37,090
I feel like

649
00:26:37,150 --> 00:26:37,940
she still hopes

650
00:26:37,940 --> 00:26:39,510
I can have a stable job.

651
00:26:39,960 --> 00:26:40,570
I'm afraid she...

652
00:26:40,570 --> 00:26:41,520
Wrong.

653
00:26:41,750 --> 00:26:43,380
Mom is much more open-minded than you.

654
00:26:43,380 --> 00:26:44,010
I guarantee

655
00:26:44,010 --> 00:26:45,330
she'll definitely support you.

656
00:26:45,330 --> 00:26:46,110
Besides,

657
00:26:46,220 --> 00:26:47,650
if you go to the saltworks,

658
00:26:47,650 --> 00:26:48,470
and if you can't find a girlfriend,

659
00:26:48,470 --> 00:26:49,830
Mom will be even more upset about it.

660
00:26:49,830 --> 00:26:51,290
I didn't think about that.

661
00:26:51,740 --> 00:26:52,740
Stop pretending.

662
00:26:52,850 --> 00:26:53,890
It's settled then.

663
00:26:53,890 --> 00:26:54,570
You stay here.

664
00:26:54,570 --> 00:26:55,030
Tomorrow, the two of us

665
00:26:55,030 --> 00:26:55,950
will go check out shop locations together

666
00:26:55,950 --> 00:26:57,750
and try to lock down a spot first.

667
00:27:00,270 --> 00:27:00,770
Okay.

668
00:27:01,540 --> 00:27:02,220
Rest, Chun.

669
00:27:02,340 --> 00:27:02,940
I'll do it.

670
00:27:08,010 --> 00:27:08,940
Is anyone there?

671
00:27:09,200 --> 00:27:10,200
Open the door!

672
00:27:12,570 --> 00:27:14,010
Is anyone there?

673
00:27:14,450 --> 00:27:15,100
Open the door!

674
00:27:15,100 --> 00:27:16,760
[Mazhi County Xinhua Copper Factory]

675
00:27:17,030 --> 00:27:17,500
Ju.

676
00:27:18,000 --> 00:27:18,670
Watch me.

677
00:27:22,690 --> 00:27:23,690
Is anyone there?

678
00:27:24,200 --> 00:27:25,240
Open the door!

679
00:27:27,040 --> 00:27:28,120
Who is it?

680
00:27:30,030 --> 00:27:30,680
Police!

681
00:27:30,950 --> 00:27:31,770
Open the door!

682
00:27:38,700 --> 00:27:39,570
Officer Bai.

683
00:27:40,290 --> 00:27:40,880
I really don't know anything

684
00:27:40,880 --> 00:27:42,480
about this mercury business

685
00:27:42,770 --> 00:27:44,030
you mentioned.

686
00:27:44,690 --> 00:27:45,620
Have some water.

687
00:27:46,550 --> 00:27:48,410
Aren't you the factory director?

688
00:27:48,410 --> 00:27:49,670
How could you not know?

689
00:27:50,180 --> 00:27:50,760
That was all

690
00:27:50,760 --> 00:27:52,070
done by the previous director.

691
00:27:52,070 --> 00:27:53,670
He was caught and sentenced.

692
00:27:53,740 --> 00:27:54,400
Please sit.

693
00:27:54,770 --> 00:27:55,500
Back then,

694
00:27:55,580 --> 00:27:56,890
because there was a market
for silver-gilt copper Buddhas,

695
00:27:56,890 --> 00:27:58,430
incense burners, and such,

696
00:27:58,450 --> 00:27:59,190
the factory

697
00:27:59,330 --> 00:28:00,660
thought about making some too

698
00:28:00,660 --> 00:28:01,860
to make a bit of money.

699
00:28:01,940 --> 00:28:02,590
But

700
00:28:02,610 --> 00:28:04,660
they didn't have the license
to buy mercury.

701
00:28:04,660 --> 00:28:05,180
So,

702
00:28:05,270 --> 00:28:07,600
they went through some other channels...

703
00:28:09,420 --> 00:28:10,200
This was

704
00:28:10,290 --> 00:28:11,090
a huge mistake

705
00:28:11,160 --> 00:28:12,490
and illegal, after all.

706
00:28:12,510 --> 00:28:13,110
In the end,

707
00:28:13,160 --> 00:28:14,530
a large fine was paid.

708
00:28:14,870 --> 00:28:15,650
The mercury

709
00:28:15,810 --> 00:28:16,660
was also confiscated

710
00:28:16,660 --> 00:28:17,730
by the police.

711
00:28:17,830 --> 00:28:18,860
The people responsible

712
00:28:18,860 --> 00:28:19,990
were all sentenced.

713
00:28:21,220 --> 00:28:22,200
But I see

714
00:28:22,290 --> 00:28:23,200
the number of seized mercury

715
00:28:23,200 --> 00:28:24,330
doesn't add up.

716
00:28:24,660 --> 00:28:25,160
You brought in

717
00:28:25,160 --> 00:28:26,140
150 kilograms.

718
00:28:26,680 --> 00:28:27,180
It was in a week's time.

719
00:28:27,180 --> 00:28:28,660
How much could you have used?

720
00:28:28,660 --> 00:28:29,740
But we only found

721
00:28:29,760 --> 00:28:30,680
50 kilograms.

722
00:28:31,070 --> 00:28:32,070
Where is the rest?

723
00:28:32,780 --> 00:28:34,390
I really don't know.

724
00:28:34,790 --> 00:28:35,440
Anyway,

725
00:28:35,530 --> 00:28:36,660
the fines were paid,

726
00:28:36,660 --> 00:28:38,120
and the sentences served.

727
00:28:38,200 --> 00:28:38,830
Everything

728
00:28:38,830 --> 00:28:40,490
was done according to the law.

729
00:28:41,420 --> 00:28:42,440
What is your factory

730
00:28:42,440 --> 00:28:43,240
doing now?

731
00:28:44,090 --> 00:28:45,030
We operate

732
00:28:45,140 --> 00:28:46,660
legally now.

733
00:28:46,750 --> 00:28:48,400
No crooked business at all.

734
00:28:48,560 --> 00:28:49,700
Do you use mercury?

735
00:28:49,720 --> 00:28:50,640
No, no, not at all.

736
00:28:50,640 --> 00:28:51,700
You must be joking.

737
00:28:51,770 --> 00:28:53,210
We wouldn't dare.

738
00:28:55,140 --> 00:28:55,680
Okay.

739
00:28:58,380 --> 00:28:59,460
Can I take a look

740
00:28:59,480 --> 00:29:00,420
at your warehouse?

741
00:29:00,420 --> 00:29:01,290
No problem.

742
00:29:01,400 --> 00:29:02,400
Look all you want.

743
00:29:02,460 --> 00:29:03,390
Watch your step.

744
00:29:04,330 --> 00:29:05,240
That's the situation

745
00:29:05,240 --> 00:29:05,940
with the factory

746
00:29:05,940 --> 00:29:07,140
now.

747
00:29:07,960 --> 00:29:08,720
Alright.

748
00:29:09,010 --> 00:29:09,750
Officer Bai,

749
00:29:10,090 --> 00:29:11,330
I won't see you out.

750
00:29:11,900 --> 00:29:12,500
Thank you.

751
00:29:12,810 --> 00:29:13,220
Okay.

752
00:29:21,980 --> 00:29:22,590
Ju.

753
00:29:22,760 --> 00:29:23,330
Is there actually something wrong

754
00:29:23,330 --> 00:29:24,460
with this factory?

755
00:29:25,590 --> 00:29:27,500
There's nothing in the warehouse.

756
00:29:27,500 --> 00:29:28,260
It feels like this factory

757
00:29:28,260 --> 00:29:29,390
is about to go under.

758
00:29:30,010 --> 00:29:31,570
The manager agreed so readily.

759
00:29:31,570 --> 00:29:32,390
I knew

760
00:29:32,690 --> 00:29:34,220
we wouldn't find anything.

761
00:29:34,590 --> 00:29:36,390
What is mercury used for anyway?

762
00:29:36,920 --> 00:29:37,870
It has many uses.

763
00:29:38,050 --> 00:29:38,790
Anyway,

764
00:29:38,840 --> 00:29:40,440
it's used for refining gold.

765
00:29:52,340 --> 00:29:53,140
What's wrong?

766
00:29:53,140 --> 00:29:54,270
Do you know that man?

767
00:29:55,550 --> 00:29:56,770
He looks familiar.

768
00:29:58,850 --> 00:30:00,050
But I can't remember.

769
00:30:06,250 --> 00:30:06,770
Ju.

770
00:30:07,040 --> 00:30:08,450
Can I have a piece of chocolate?

771
00:30:08,450 --> 00:30:09,910
I see some in the glove box.

772
00:30:10,010 --> 00:30:10,600
Just eat.

773
00:30:15,670 --> 00:30:16,780
I remember Shao Yunfei's

774
00:30:16,780 --> 00:30:18,060
package

775
00:30:18,340 --> 00:30:19,530
had a share for you.

776
00:30:24,220 --> 00:30:25,420
You're being greedy.

777
00:30:27,700 --> 00:30:29,180
I haven't touched my share yet.

778
00:30:29,180 --> 00:30:30,780
Then why are you eating mine?

779
00:30:31,250 --> 00:30:32,250
I've never had

780
00:30:32,530 --> 00:30:33,500
this before.

781
00:30:34,330 --> 00:30:36,190
It's my first time even seeing it.

782
00:30:36,580 --> 00:30:38,840
You make it sound like I've had it before.

783
00:30:42,440 --> 00:30:44,240
My brother hasn't had it either.

784
00:30:51,750 --> 00:30:52,380
If you keep holding it,

785
00:30:52,380 --> 00:30:53,440
it's going to melt.

786
00:30:55,510 --> 00:30:56,250
Eat it.

787
00:30:56,960 --> 00:30:58,760
I have more if that's not enough.

788
00:30:59,920 --> 00:31:00,580
Thanks, Ju.

789
00:31:06,110 --> 00:31:06,770
Delicious.

790
00:31:08,900 --> 00:31:10,760
Ju, you're actually pretty nice.

791
00:31:11,160 --> 00:31:12,270
You just realized?

792
00:31:12,380 --> 00:31:13,790
You just have a sharp tongue.

793
00:31:13,790 --> 00:31:14,350
Spit the chocolate out

794
00:31:14,350 --> 00:31:14,950
right now.

795
00:31:14,960 --> 00:31:15,830
Look, look.

796
00:31:15,880 --> 00:31:16,740
Just like that.

797
00:31:19,510 --> 00:31:20,010
Ju.

798
00:31:20,440 --> 00:31:21,700
Once I find my brother,

799
00:31:22,290 --> 00:31:23,010
I'll do

800
00:31:23,030 --> 00:31:24,030
whatever you ask.

801
00:31:24,790 --> 00:31:25,570
Come on.

802
00:31:26,400 --> 00:31:27,730
I just have one request.

803
00:31:28,920 --> 00:31:30,940
Don't go to the Uninhabited Zone anymore.

804
00:31:30,940 --> 00:31:31,590
I won't.

805
00:31:34,010 --> 00:31:35,020
I want to take my brother

806
00:31:35,020 --> 00:31:36,110
to a big city.

807
00:31:36,550 --> 00:31:37,550
I want to work

808
00:31:37,950 --> 00:31:39,280
to support his studies.

809
00:31:41,430 --> 00:31:42,890
My sister is in Guangzhou.

810
00:31:43,030 --> 00:31:44,240
If you want to work later,

811
00:31:44,240 --> 00:31:45,480
I'll ask my sister for you.

812
00:31:45,480 --> 00:31:46,240
Really, Ju?

813
00:31:46,330 --> 00:31:47,400
But if you don't behave,

814
00:31:47,400 --> 00:31:48,660
I'll have her beat you.

815
00:32:01,550 --> 00:32:02,550
What's wrong, Ju?

816
00:32:02,900 --> 00:32:03,700
What's wrong?

817
00:32:05,960 --> 00:32:06,610
Hold on!

818
00:32:07,030 --> 00:32:07,640
Sit tight!

819
00:32:09,450 --> 00:32:10,830
Stop the car! Stop now!

820
00:32:10,850 --> 00:32:11,550
Stop!

821
00:32:11,890 --> 00:32:12,480
Stop!

822
00:33:01,740 --> 00:33:02,310
Ju!

823
00:33:03,050 --> 00:33:03,680
Ju!

824
00:33:04,510 --> 00:33:05,110
Ju!

825
00:33:08,700 --> 00:33:09,630
Is anyone there?

826
00:33:10,810 --> 00:33:11,830
Help!

827
00:33:32,330 --> 00:33:32,880
Ju!

828
00:33:33,570 --> 00:33:34,090
Ju!

829
00:33:34,680 --> 00:33:35,790
Ju, wake up!

830
00:33:36,090 --> 00:33:36,700
Ju!

831
00:33:37,440 --> 00:33:38,090
Ju!

832
00:33:40,310 --> 00:33:41,310
Help!

833
00:33:43,290 --> 00:33:44,400
Is anyone there?

834
00:33:56,530 --> 00:33:57,740
Is anyone there?

835
00:34:02,240 --> 00:34:03,440
Is anyone there?

836
00:34:17,400 --> 00:34:18,300
Help!

837
00:34:19,800 --> 00:34:20,610
Stop the car!

838
00:34:21,010 --> 00:34:22,920
Stop the car! Stop the car!

839
00:34:29,040 --> 00:34:31,250
Stop the car! Help!

840
00:34:33,000 --> 00:34:34,110
Help!

841
00:35:20,090 --> 00:35:20,510
Captain.

842
00:35:20,510 --> 00:35:21,040
Captain.

843
00:35:21,550 --> 00:35:22,000
County Mayor Duo.

844
00:35:22,000 --> 00:35:22,730
How are they?

845
00:35:23,210 --> 00:35:24,470
Bai Ju is out of danger.

846
00:35:24,900 --> 00:35:27,300
Zhang Yang is still in critical condition.

847
00:35:27,840 --> 00:35:29,170
What exactly happened?

848
00:35:29,400 --> 00:35:30,360
County Mayor Duo,

849
00:35:30,360 --> 00:35:31,170
based on the preliminary investigation

850
00:35:31,170 --> 00:35:32,470
of the accident scene,

851
00:35:32,570 --> 00:35:33,330
this

852
00:35:33,420 --> 00:35:34,510
is a hit-and-run case.

853
00:35:34,510 --> 00:35:36,250
This is definitely not
just a traffic accident!

854
00:35:36,250 --> 00:35:37,300
How can there be 2 traffic accidents

855
00:35:37,300 --> 00:35:38,300
happening one after another?

856
00:35:38,300 --> 00:35:39,150
Retaliation!

857
00:35:39,170 --> 00:35:40,520
This is retaliation!

858
00:35:40,550 --> 00:35:40,900
Zhacuo!

859
00:35:40,900 --> 00:35:41,380
Officer,

860
00:35:41,380 --> 00:35:42,650
we can't just let this go!

861
00:35:42,650 --> 00:35:43,310
Calm down!

862
00:35:43,340 --> 00:35:44,260
Listen to me!

863
00:35:44,710 --> 00:35:45,670
I understand

864
00:35:45,690 --> 00:35:46,670
how you feel now.

865
00:35:47,000 --> 00:35:49,010
But the scene
is currently under investigation.

866
00:35:49,010 --> 00:35:49,960
There is no evidence to prove

867
00:35:49,960 --> 00:35:51,230
whether it is intentional

868
00:35:51,230 --> 00:35:52,920
or a hit-and-run.

869
00:35:53,010 --> 00:35:54,730
We just can't classify it yet.

870
00:35:58,510 --> 00:35:59,510
County Mayor Duo,

871
00:36:00,170 --> 00:36:01,580
I hope you can

872
00:36:01,800 --> 00:36:02,530
understand.

873
00:36:09,050 --> 00:36:10,050
How is Zhang Yang?

874
00:36:12,590 --> 00:36:14,190
He has something to tell you.

875
00:36:14,840 --> 00:36:16,200
Go in and take a look.

876
00:36:32,110 --> 00:36:32,910
You're awake?

877
00:36:35,360 --> 00:36:36,500
How do you feel now?

878
00:36:38,260 --> 00:36:39,060
Are you dizzy?

879
00:36:45,230 --> 00:36:45,730
You...

880
00:36:47,230 --> 00:36:47,860
Me?

881
00:36:49,110 --> 00:36:50,760
It's Shao Yunfei. I'm back.

882
00:36:52,110 --> 00:36:53,310
You're not dreaming.

883
00:37:00,440 --> 00:37:01,390
No, no, no.

884
00:37:01,420 --> 00:37:02,570
You can't. You can't.

885
00:37:02,570 --> 00:37:03,430
You can't move.

886
00:37:04,170 --> 00:37:04,730
Auntie said

887
00:37:04,730 --> 00:37:05,480
you have a concussion

888
00:37:05,480 --> 00:37:06,760
and need to rest well.

889
00:37:09,420 --> 00:37:10,420
My mom?

890
00:37:11,110 --> 00:37:12,150
Auntie said

891
00:37:13,230 --> 00:37:14,710
it's just superficial wounds.

892
00:37:14,710 --> 00:37:15,640
No broken bones.

893
00:37:26,320 --> 00:37:27,450
